      "locked": false,
      "text": "6) \na ) what is JSON .... explain with an example\n\n- > Javascript Object notation \n -> JSON is a light-weighted data-interchange format used to store and exchange \n    data. \n-> it is text based , easy to read , and language-independent . \n\nStructure \n    Objects -- >   enclosed in curly braces { }.\n    Arrays/Dict. --> enclosed in square brackets [ ]\n    Data are stores in key-value pairs\n            ==> Key must be a string ( in double quotes)\n            ==> value can be :\n                      > String \n                      > Number \n                      > Boolean \n                      > Object \n                      > Arrtay/Dict.\n\nExample:\n      \n",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "6) \na ) what is JSON .... explain with an example\n\n- > Javascript Object notation \n -> JSON is a light-weighted data-interchange format used to store and exchange \n    data. \n-> it is text based , easy to read , and language-independent . \n\nStructure \n    Objects -- >   enclosed in curly braces { }.\n    Arrays/Dict. --> enclosed in square brackets [ ]\n    Data are stores in key-value pairs\n            ==> Key must be a string ( in double quotes)\n            ==> value can be :\n                      > String \n                      > Number \n                      > Boolean \n                      > Object \n                      > Arrtay/Dict.\n\nExample:\n      \n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
