      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "(b) What is the Purpose of Container?\nPurpose of Container\n\nIn Flutter, a Container is a layout widget used to store and design other widgets.\nIt is mainly used for:\n\n- Adding padding and margin\n\n- Setting height and width\n\n- Applying background color\n\n- Adding borders\n\n- Aligning child widgets\n\nIt acts as a customizable box for UI design.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "(b) What is the Purpose of Container?\nPurpose of Container\n\nIn Flutter, a Container is a layout widget used to store and design other widgets.\nIt is mainly used for:\n\n- Adding padding and margin\n\n- Setting height and width\n\n- Applying background color\n\n- Adding borders\n\n- Aligning child widgets\n\nIt acts as a customizable box for UI design.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
